text: John Eric Maenchen is an electrical engineer with Sandia National Laboratories in Arlington, Virginia. He was named a Fellow of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE) in 2012 for his work in the development of intense pulsed charged particle beams, and their application for flash radiography. == References == Category:Fellow Members of the IEEE Category:Sandia National Laboratories people Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
